    <template>The first-line treatment for type 2 diabetes is diet, weight control and physical activity. If your blood glucose level remains high despite a trial of these lifestyle measures then tablets to reduce the blood glucose level are usually advised. Insulin injections are needed in some cases if the blood glucose level remains too high despite taking tablets.
    </template>
