              Do I need to monitor my blood sugar when I have type 2 diabetes
    </pattern>
    <template> You may feel fine, but that is no guarantee that your blood sugar levels are in the target range. 
	Diabetic complications do not appear right away. And complications may develop even when the blood sugar is only slightly elevated. 
	Regular blood sugar monitoring can help you keep your blood sugars in control and prevent serious damage to your eyes, kidneys and nerves. If your sugar levels are out of line, consult your doctor.
    </template>
